115static bool isInterchangeNewlineNode(const Node* node)
116{
117 static NeverDestroyed<String> interchangeNewlineClassString(AppleInterchangeNewline);
118 return is<HTMLBRElement>(node) && downcast<HTMLBRElement>(*node).attributeWithoutSynchronization(classAttr) == interchangeNewlineClassString;
119}

121static bool isInterchangeConvertedSpaceSpan(const Node* node)
122{
123 static NeverDestroyed<String> convertedSpaceSpanClassString(AppleConvertedSpace);
124 return is<HTMLElement>(node) && downcast<HTMLElement>(*node).attributeWithoutSynchronization(classAttr) == convertedSpaceSpanClassString;
125}

127static Position positionAvoidingPrecedingNodes(Position position)
128{
129 ASSERT(position.isNotNull());
130
131 // If we're already on a break, it's probably a placeholder and we shouldn't change our position.
132 if (editingIgnoresContent(*position.deprecatedNode()))
133 return position;
134
135 // We also stop when changing block flow elements because even though the visual position is the
136 // same. E.g.,
137 // <div>foo^</div>^
138 // The two positions above are the same visual position, but we want to stay in the same block.
139 auto enclosingBlockNode = makeRefPtr(enclosingBlock(position.containerNode()));
140 for (Position nextPosition = position; nextPosition.containerNode() != enclosingBlockNode; position = nextPosition) {
141 if (lineBreakExistsAtPosition(position))
142 break;
143
144 if (position.containerNode()->nonShadowBoundaryParentNode())
145 nextPosition = positionInParentAfterNode(position.containerNode());
146
147 if (nextPosition == position)
148 break;
149 if (enclosingBlock(nextPosition.containerNode()) != enclosingBlockNode)
150 break;
151 if (VisiblePosition(position) != VisiblePosition(nextPosition))
152 break;
153 }
154 return position;
155}

157ReplacementFragment::ReplacementFragment(DocumentFragment* fragment, const VisibleSelection& selection)
158 : m_fragment(fragment)
159 , m_hasInterchangeNewlineAtStart(false)
160 , m_hasInterchangeNewlineAtEnd(false)
161{
162 if (!m_fragment)
163 return;
164 if (!m_fragment->firstChild())
165 return;
166
167 removeContentsWithSideEffects();
168
169 RefPtr<Element> editableRoot = selection.rootEditableElement();
170 ASSERT(editableRoot);
171 if (!editableRoot)
172 return;
173
174 auto shadowHost = makeRefPtr(editableRoot->shadowHost());
175 if (!editableRoot->attributeEventListener(eventNames().webkitBeforeTextInsertedEvent, mainThreadNormalWorld())
176 && !(shadowHost && shadowHost->renderer() && shadowHost->renderer()->isTextControl())
177 && editableRoot->hasRichlyEditableStyle()) {
178 removeInterchangeNodes(m_fragment.get());
179 return;
180 }
181
182 auto page = createPageForSanitizingWebContent();
183 auto stagingDocument = makeRefPtr(page->mainFrame().document());
184 ASSERT(stagingDocument->body());
185
186 ComputedStyleExtractor computedStyleOfEditableRoot(editableRoot.get());
187 stagingDocument->body()->setAttributeWithoutSynchronization(styleAttr, computedStyleOfEditableRoot.copyProperties()->asText());
188
189 RefPtr<StyledElement> holder = insertFragmentForTestRendering(stagingDocument->body());
190 if (!holder) {
191 removeInterchangeNodes(m_fragment.get());
192 return;
193 }
194
195 auto range = VisibleSelection::selectionFromContentsOfNode(holder.get()).toNormalizedRange();
196 String text = range ? plainText(*range, { TextIteratorBehavior::EmitsOriginalText, TextIteratorBehavior::IgnoresStyleVisibility }) : emptyString();
197
198 removeInterchangeNodes(holder.get());
199 removeUnrenderedNodes(holder.get());
200 restoreAndRemoveTestRenderingNodesToFragment(holder.get());
201
202 // Give the root a chance to change the text.
203 auto event = BeforeTextInsertedEvent::create(text);
204 editableRoot->dispatchEvent(event);
205 if (text != event->text() || !editableRoot->hasRichlyEditableStyle()) {
206 restoreAndRemoveTestRenderingNodesToFragment(holder.get());
207
208 auto range = selection.toNormalizedRange();
209 if (!range)
210 return;
211
212 m_fragment = createFragmentFromText(*range, event->text());
213 if (!m_fragment->firstChild())
214 return;
215
216 holder = insertFragmentForTestRendering(stagingDocument->body());
217 removeInterchangeNodes(holder.get());
218 removeUnrenderedNodes(holder.get());
219 restoreAndRemoveTestRenderingNodesToFragment(holder.get());
220 }
221}
222
223void ReplacementFragment::removeContentsWithSideEffects()
224{
225 Vector<Ref<Element>> elementsToRemove;
226 Vector<std::pair<Ref<Element>, QualifiedName>> attributesToRemove;
227
228 auto it = descendantsOfType<Element>(*m_fragment).begin();
229 auto end = descendantsOfType<Element>(*m_fragment).end();
230 while (it != end) {
231 auto element = makeRef(*it);
232 if (isScriptElement(element) || (is<HTMLStyleElement>(element) && element->getAttribute(classAttr) != WebKitMSOListQuirksStyle)
233 || is<HTMLBaseElement>(element) || is<HTMLLinkElement>(element) || is<HTMLMetaElement>(element) || is<HTMLTitleElement>(element)) {
234 elementsToRemove.append(WTFMove(element));
235 it.traverseNextSkippingChildren();
236 continue;
237 }
238 if (element->hasAttributes()) {
239 for (auto& attribute : element->attributesIterator()) {
240 if (element->isEventHandlerAttribute(attribute) || element->isJavaScriptURLAttribute(attribute))
241 attributesToRemove.append({ element.copyRef(), attribute.name() });
242 }
243 }
244 ++it;
245 }
246
247 for (auto& element : elementsToRemove)
248 removeNode(WTFMove(element));
249
250 for (auto& item : attributesToRemove)
251 item.first->removeAttribute(item.second);
252}

254bool ReplacementFragment::isEmpty() const
255{
256 return (!m_fragment || !m_fragment->firstChild()) && !m_hasInterchangeNewlineAtStart && !m_hasInterchangeNewlineAtEnd;
257}

259Node *ReplacementFragment::firstChild() const

261 return m_fragment ? m_fragment->firstChild() : 0;

264Node *ReplacementFragment::lastChild() const
265{
266 return m_fragment ? m_fragment->lastChild() : 0;

269void ReplacementFragment::removeNodePreservingChildren(Node& node)
270{
271 Ref<Node> protectedNode = node;
272 while (RefPtr<Node> n = node.firstChild()) {
273 removeNode(*n);
274 insertNodeBefore(*n, node);
275 }
276 removeNode(node);
277}
278
279void ReplacementFragment::removeNode(Node& node)
280{
281 ContainerNode* parent = node.nonShadowBoundaryParentNode();
282 if (!parent)
283 return;
284
285 parent->removeChild(node);
286}
287
288void ReplacementFragment::insertNodeBefore(Node& node, Node& refNode)
289{
290 ContainerNode* parent = refNode.nonShadowBoundaryParentNode();
291 if (!parent)
292 return;
293
294 parent->insertBefore(node, &refNode);
295}

297Ref<HTMLElement> ReplacementFragment::insertFragmentForTestRendering(Node* rootNode)
298{
299 auto document = makeRef(rootNode->document());
300 auto holder = createDefaultParagraphElement(document.get());
301
302 holder->appendChild(*m_fragment);
303 rootNode->appendChild(holder);
304 document->updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
305
306 return holder;
307}
308
309void ReplacementFragment::restoreAndRemoveTestRenderingNodesToFragment(StyledElement* holder)
310{
311 if (!holder)
312 return;
313
314 while (RefPtr<Node> node = holder->firstChild()) {
315 holder->removeChild(*node);
316 m_fragment->appendChild(*node);
317 }
318
319 removeNode(*holder);
320}
321
322void ReplacementFragment::removeUnrenderedNodes(Node* holder)
323{
324 Vector<Ref<Node>> unrendered;
325
326 for (auto node = makeRefPtr(holder->firstChild()); node; node = NodeTraversal::next(*node, holder)) {
327 if (!isNodeRendered(*node) && !isTableStructureNode(node.get()))
328 unrendered.append(*node);
329 }
330
331 for (auto& node : unrendered)
332 removeNode(node);
333}
334
335void ReplacementFragment::removeInterchangeNodes(Node* container)
336{
337 m_hasInterchangeNewlineAtStart = false;
338 m_hasInterchangeNewlineAtEnd = false;
339
340 // Interchange newlines at the "start" of the incoming fragment must be
341 // either the first node in the fragment or the first leaf in the fragment.
342 auto node = makeRefPtr(container->firstChild());
343 while (node) {
344 if (isInterchangeNewlineNode(node.get())) {
345 m_hasInterchangeNewlineAtStart = true;
346 removeNode(*node);
347 break;
348 }
349 node = node->firstChild();
350 }
351 if (!container->hasChildNodes())
352 return;
353 // Interchange newlines at the "end" of the incoming fragment must be
354 // either the last node in the fragment or the last leaf in the fragment.
355 node = container->lastChild();
356 while (node) {
357 if (isInterchangeNewlineNode(node.get())) {
358 m_hasInterchangeNewlineAtEnd = true;
359 removeNode(*node);
360 break;
361 }
362 node = node->lastChild();
363 }
364
365 node = container->firstChild();
366 while (node) {
367 RefPtr<Node> next = NodeTraversal::next(*node);
368 if (isInterchangeConvertedSpaceSpan(node.get())) {
369 next = NodeTraversal::nextSkippingChildren(*node);
370 removeNodePreservingChildren(*node);
371 }
372 node = WTFMove(next);
373 }
374}

376inline void ReplaceSelectionCommand::InsertedNodes::respondToNodeInsertion(Node* node)
377{
378 if (!node)
379 return;
380
381 if (!m_firstNodeInserted)
382 m_firstNodeInserted = node;
383
384 m_lastNodeInserted = node;
385}
386
387inline void ReplaceSelectionCommand::InsertedNodes::willRemoveNodePreservingChildren(Node* node)
388{
389 if (m_firstNodeInserted == node)
390 m_firstNodeInserted = NodeTraversal::next(*node);
391 if (m_lastNodeInserted == node) {
392 m_lastNodeInserted = node->lastChild() ? node->lastChild() : NodeTraversal::nextSkippingChildren(*node);
393 if (!m_lastNodeInserted && m_firstNodeInserted) {
394 // If the last inserted node is at the end of the document and doesn't have any children, look backwards for the
395 // previous node as the last inserted node, clamping to the first inserted node if needed to ensure that the
396 // document position of the last inserted node is not behind the first inserted node.
397 auto* previousNode = NodeTraversal::previousSkippingChildren(*node);
398 ASSERT(previousNode);
399 m_lastNodeInserted = m_firstNodeInserted->compareDocumentPosition(*previousNode) & Node::DOCUMENT_POSITION_FOLLOWING ? previousNode : m_firstNodeInserted;
400 }
401 }
402}
403
404inline void ReplaceSelectionCommand::InsertedNodes::willRemovePossibleAncestorNode(Node* node)
405{
406 bool containsFirstNode = node->contains(m_firstNodeInserted.get());
407 bool containsLastNode = node->contains(m_lastNodeInserted.get());
408 if (containsFirstNode && containsLastNode) {
409 m_firstNodeInserted = nullptr;
410 m_lastNodeInserted = nullptr;
411 return;
412 }
413
414 if (containsLastNode)
415 m_lastNodeInserted = NodeTraversal::previousSkippingChildren(*node);
416 else if (containsFirstNode)
417 m_firstNodeInserted = NodeTraversal::nextSkippingChildren(*node);
418
419 if (!m_lastNodeInserted)
420 m_lastNodeInserted = m_firstNodeInserted;
421 else if (!m_firstNodeInserted)
422 m_firstNodeInserted = m_lastNodeInserted;
423 else if (m_firstNodeInserted->isDescendantOf(m_lastNodeInserted.get()))
424 std::swap(m_firstNodeInserted, m_lastNodeInserted);
425}
426
427inline void ReplaceSelectionCommand::InsertedNodes::willRemoveNode(Node* node)
428{
429 ASSERT(!m_firstNodeInserted || !m_firstNodeInserted->isDescendantOf(node));
430 ASSERT(!m_lastNodeInserted || !m_lastNodeInserted->isDescendantOf(node));
431
432 if (m_firstNodeInserted == node && m_lastNodeInserted == node) {
433 m_firstNodeInserted = nullptr;
434 m_lastNodeInserted = nullptr;
435 } else if (m_firstNodeInserted == node)
436 m_firstNodeInserted = NodeTraversal::nextSkippingChildren(*m_firstNodeInserted);
437 else if (m_lastNodeInserted == node)
438 m_lastNodeInserted = NodeTraversal::previousSkippingChildren(*m_lastNodeInserted);
439}
440
441inline void ReplaceSelectionCommand::InsertedNodes::didReplaceNode(Node* node, Node* newNode)
442{
443 if (m_firstNodeInserted == node)
444 m_firstNodeInserted = newNode;
445 if (m_lastNodeInserted == node)
446 m_lastNodeInserted = newNode;
447}

463static bool hasMatchingQuoteLevel(VisiblePosition endOfExistingContent, VisiblePosition endOfInsertedContent)
464{
465 Position existing = endOfExistingContent.deepEquivalent();
466 Position inserted = endOfInsertedContent.deepEquivalent();
467 bool isInsideMailBlockquote = enclosingNodeOfType(inserted, isMailBlockquote, CanCrossEditingBoundary);
468 return isInsideMailBlockquote && (numEnclosingMailBlockquotes(existing) == numEnclosingMailBlockquotes(inserted));
469}
470
471bool ReplaceSelectionCommand::shouldMergeStart(bool selectionStartWasStartOfParagraph, bool fragmentHasInterchangeNewlineAtStart, bool selectionStartWasInsideMailBlockquote)
472{
473 if (m_movingParagraph)
474 return false;
475
476 VisiblePosition startOfInsertedContent(positionAtStartOfInsertedContent());
477 VisiblePosition prev = startOfInsertedContent.previous(CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
478 if (prev.isNull())
479 return false;
480
481 // When we have matching quote levels, its ok to merge more frequently.
482 // For a successful merge, we still need to make sure that the inserted content starts with the beginning of a paragraph.
483 // And we should only merge here if the selection start was inside a mail blockquote. This prevents against removing a
484 // blockquote from newly pasted quoted content that was pasted into an unquoted position. If that unquoted position happens
485 // to be right after another blockquote, we don't want to merge and risk stripping a valid block (and newline) from the pasted content.
486 if (isStartOfParagraph(startOfInsertedContent) && selectionStartWasInsideMailBlockquote && hasMatchingQuoteLevel(prev, positionAtEndOfInsertedContent()))
487 return true;
488
489 return !selectionStartWasStartOfParagraph
490 && !fragmentHasInterchangeNewlineAtStart
491 && isStartOfParagraph(startOfInsertedContent)
492 && !startOfInsertedContent.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode()->hasTagName(brTag)
493 && shouldMerge(startOfInsertedContent, prev);
494}
495
496bool ReplaceSelectionCommand::shouldMergeEnd(bool selectionEndWasEndOfParagraph)
497{
498 VisiblePosition endOfInsertedContent(positionAtEndOfInsertedContent());
499 VisiblePosition next = endOfInsertedContent.next(CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
500 if (next.isNull())
501 return false;
502
503 return !selectionEndWasEndOfParagraph
504 && isEndOfParagraph(endOfInsertedContent)
505 && !endOfInsertedContent.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode()->hasTagName(brTag)
506 && shouldMerge(endOfInsertedContent, next);
507}

509static bool isMailPasteAsQuotationNode(const Node* node)
510{
511 return node && node->hasTagName(blockquoteTag) && downcast<Element>(node)->attributeWithoutSynchronization(classAttr) == ApplePasteAsQuotation;
512}

514static bool isHeaderElement(const Node* a)
515{
516 if (!a)
517 return false;
518
519 return a->hasTagName(h1Tag)
520 || a->hasTagName(h2Tag)
521 || a->hasTagName(h3Tag)
522 || a->hasTagName(h4Tag)
523 || a->hasTagName(h5Tag)
524 || a->hasTagName(h6Tag);
525}
526
527static bool haveSameTagName(Node* a, Node* b)
528{
529 return is<Element>(a) && is<Element>(b) && downcast<Element>(*a).tagName() == downcast<Element>(*b).tagName();
530}
531
532bool ReplaceSelectionCommand::shouldMerge(const VisiblePosition& source, const VisiblePosition& destination)
533{
534 if (source.isNull() || destination.isNull())
535 return false;
536
537 auto sourceNode = makeRefPtr(source.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode());
538 auto destinationNode = makeRefPtr(destination.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode());
539 auto sourceBlock = makeRefPtr(enclosingBlock(sourceNode.get()));
540 auto destinationBlock = makeRefPtr(enclosingBlock(destinationNode.get()));
541 return !enclosingNodeOfType(source.deepEquivalent(), &isMailPasteAsQuotationNode)
542 && sourceBlock
543 && (!sourceBlock->hasTagName(blockquoteTag) || isMailBlockquote(sourceBlock.get()))
544 && enclosingListChild(sourceBlock.get()) == enclosingListChild(destinationNode.get())
545 && enclosingTableCell(source.deepEquivalent()) == enclosingTableCell(destination.deepEquivalent())
546 && (!isHeaderElement(sourceBlock.get()) || haveSameTagName(sourceBlock.get(), destinationBlock.get()))
547 // Don't merge to or from a position before or after a block because it would
548 // be a no-op and cause infinite recursion.
549 && !isBlock(sourceNode.get()) && !isBlock(destinationNode.get());
550}

552static bool fragmentNeedsColorTransformed(ReplacementFragment& fragment, const Position& insertionPos)
553{
554 // Dark mode content that is inserted should have the inline styles inverse color
555 // transformed by the color filter to match the color filtered document contents.
556 // This applies to Mail and Notes when pasting from Xcode. <rdar://problem/40529867>
557
558 RefPtr<Element> editableRoot = insertionPos.rootEditableElement();
559 if (!editableRoot)
560 return false;
561
562 {
563 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
564
565 auto* editableRootRenderer = editableRoot->renderer();
566 if (!editableRootRenderer || !editableRootRenderer->style().hasAppleColorFilter())
567 return false;
568
569 const auto& colorFilter = editableRootRenderer->style().appleColorFilter();
570 for (const auto& colorFilterOperation : colorFilter.operations()) {
571 if (colorFilterOperation->type() != FilterOperation::APPLE_INVERT_LIGHTNESS)
572 return false;
573 }
574 }
575
576 auto propertyLightness = [&](const StyleProperties& inlineStyle, CSSPropertyID propertyID) -> std::optional<double> {
577 auto color = inlineStyle.propertyAsColor(propertyID);
578 if (!color || !color.value().isVisible() || color.value().isSemantic())
579 return { };
580
581 return color.value().lightness();
582 };
583
584 const double lightnessDarkEnoughForText = 0.4;
585 const double lightnessLightEnoughForBackground = 0.6;
586
587 for (RefPtr<Node> node = fragment.firstChild(); node; node = NodeTraversal::next(*node)) {
588 if (!is<StyledElement>(*node))
589 continue;
590
591 auto& element = downcast<StyledElement>(*node);
592 auto* inlineStyle = element.inlineStyle();
593 if (!inlineStyle)
594 continue;
595
596 auto textLightness = propertyLightness(*inlineStyle, CSSPropertyColor);
597 if (textLightness && *textLightness < lightnessDarkEnoughForText)
598 return false;
599
600 auto backgroundLightness = propertyLightness(*inlineStyle, CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
601 if (backgroundLightness && *backgroundLightness > lightnessLightEnoughForBackground)
602 return false;
603 }
604
605 return true;
606}
607
608void ReplaceSelectionCommand::inverseTransformColor(InsertedNodes& insertedNodes)
609{
610 RefPtr<Node> pastEndNode = insertedNodes.pastLastLeaf();
611 for (RefPtr<Node> node = insertedNodes.firstNodeInserted(); node && node != pastEndNode; node = NodeTraversal::next(*node)) {
612 if (!is<StyledElement>(*node))
613 continue;
614
615 auto& element = downcast<StyledElement>(*node);
616 auto* inlineStyle = element.inlineStyle();
617 if (!inlineStyle)
618 continue;
619
620 auto editingStyle = EditingStyle::create(inlineStyle);
621 auto transformedStyle = editingStyle->inverseTransformColorIfNeeded(element);
622 if (editingStyle.ptr() == transformedStyle.ptr())
623 continue;
624
625 setNodeAttribute(element, styleAttr, transformedStyle->style()->asText());
626 }
627}

629// Style rules that match just inserted elements could change their appearance, like
630// a div inserted into a document with div { display:inline; }.
631void ReplaceSelectionCommand::removeRedundantStylesAndKeepStyleSpanInline(InsertedNodes& insertedNodes)
632{
633 RefPtr<Node> pastEndNode = insertedNodes.pastLastLeaf();
634 RefPtr<Node> next;
635 for (RefPtr<Node> node = insertedNodes.firstNodeInserted(); node && node != pastEndNode; node = next) {
636 // FIXME: <rdar://problem/5371536> Style rules that match pasted content can change it's appearance
637
638 next = NodeTraversal::next(*node);
639 if (!is<StyledElement>(*node))
640 continue;
641
642 StyledElement* element = downcast<StyledElement>(node.get());
643
644 auto inlineStyle = makeRefPtr(element->inlineStyle());
645 auto newInlineStyle = EditingStyle::create(inlineStyle.get());
646 if (inlineStyle) {
647 if (is<HTMLElement>(*element)) {
648 Vector<QualifiedName> attributes;
649 HTMLElement& htmlElement = downcast<HTMLElement>(*element);
650
651 if (newInlineStyle->conflictsWithImplicitStyleOfElement(htmlElement)) {
652 // e.g. <b style="font-weight: normal;"> is converted to <span style="font-weight: normal;">
653 node = replaceElementWithSpanPreservingChildrenAndAttributes(htmlElement);
654 element = downcast<StyledElement>(node.get());
655 insertedNodes.didReplaceNode(&htmlElement, node.get());
656 } else if (newInlineStyle->extractConflictingImplicitStyleOfAttributes(htmlElement, EditingStyle::PreserveWritingDirection, nullptr, attributes, EditingStyle::DoNotExtractMatchingStyle)) {
657 // e.g. <font size="3" style="font-size: 20px;"> is converted to <font style="font-size: 20px;">
658 for (auto& attribute : attributes)
659 removeNodeAttribute(*element, attribute);
660 }
661 }
662
663 auto context = makeRefPtr(element->parentNode());
664
665 // If Mail wraps the fragment with a Paste as Quotation blockquote, or if you're pasting into a quoted region,
666 // styles from blockquoteNode are allowed to override those from the source document, see <rdar://problem/4930986> and <rdar://problem/5089327>.
667 RefPtr<Node> blockquoteNode = isMailPasteAsQuotationNode(context.get()) ? context.get() : enclosingNodeOfType(firstPositionInNode(context.get()), isMailBlockquote, CanCrossEditingBoundary);
668 if (blockquoteNode)
669 newInlineStyle->removeStyleFromRulesAndContext(*element, document().documentElement());
670
671 newInlineStyle->removeStyleFromRulesAndContext(*element, context.get());
672 }
673
674 if (!inlineStyle || newInlineStyle->isEmpty()) {
675 if (isStyleSpanOrSpanWithOnlyStyleAttribute(*element) || isEmptyFontTag(element, AllowNonEmptyStyleAttribute)) {
676 insertedNodes.willRemoveNodePreservingChildren(element);
677 removeNodePreservingChildren(*element);
678 continue;
679 }
680 removeNodeAttribute(*element, styleAttr);
681 } else if (newInlineStyle->style()->propertyCount() != inlineStyle->propertyCount())
682 setNodeAttribute(*element, styleAttr, newInlineStyle->style()->asText());
683
684 // FIXME: Tolerate differences in id, class, and style attributes.
685 if (element->parentNode() && isNonTableCellHTMLBlockElement(element) && areIdenticalElements(*element, *element->parentNode())
686 && VisiblePosition(firstPositionInNode(element->parentNode())) == VisiblePosition(firstPositionInNode(element))
687 && VisiblePosition(lastPositionInNode(element->parentNode())) == VisiblePosition(lastPositionInNode(element))) {
688 insertedNodes.willRemoveNodePreservingChildren(element);
689 removeNodePreservingChildren(*element);
690 continue;
691 }
692
693 if (element->parentNode() && element->parentNode()->hasRichlyEditableStyle())
694 removeNodeAttribute(*element, contenteditableAttr);
695
696 // WebKit used to not add display: inline and float: none on copy.
697 // Keep this code around for backward compatibility
698 if (isLegacyAppleStyleSpan(element)) {
699 if (!element->firstChild()) {
700 insertedNodes.willRemoveNodePreservingChildren(element);
701 removeNodePreservingChildren(*element);
702 continue;
703 }
704 // There are other styles that style rules can give to style spans,
705 // but these are the two important ones because they'll prevent
706 // inserted content from appearing in the right paragraph.
707 // FIXME: Hyatt is concerned that selectively using display:inline will give inconsistent
708 // results. We already know one issue because td elements ignore their display property
709 // in quirks mode (which Mail.app is always in). We should look for an alternative.
710
711 // Mutate using the CSSOM wrapper so we get the same event behavior as a script.
712 if (isBlock(element))
713 element->cssomStyle().setPropertyInternal(CSSPropertyDisplay, "inline", false);
714 if (element->renderer() && element->renderer()->style().isFloating())
715 element->cssomStyle().setPropertyInternal(CSSPropertyFloat, "none", false);
716 }
717 }
718}

781
782void ReplaceSelectionCommand::makeInsertedContentRoundTrippableWithHTMLTreeBuilder(InsertedNodes& insertedNodes)
783{
784 RefPtr<Node> pastEndNode = insertedNodes.pastLastLeaf();
785 RefPtr<Node> next;
786 for (RefPtr<Node> node = insertedNodes.firstNodeInserted(); node && node != pastEndNode; node = next) {
787 next = NodeTraversal::next(*node);
788
789 if (!is<HTMLElement>(*node))
790 continue;
791
792 if (isProhibitedParagraphChild(downcast<HTMLElement>(*node).localName())) {
793 if (auto paragraphElement = makeRefPtr(enclosingElementWithTag(positionInParentBeforeNode(node.get()), pTag))) {
794 auto parent = makeRefPtr(paragraphElement->parentNode());
795 if (parent && parent->hasEditableStyle())
796 moveNodeOutOfAncestor(*node, *paragraphElement, insertedNodes);
797 }
798 }
799
800 if (isHeaderElement(node.get())) {
801 if (auto headerElement = makeRefPtr(highestEnclosingNodeOfType(positionInParentBeforeNode(node.get()), isHeaderElement))) {
802 if (headerElement->parentNode() && headerElement->parentNode()->isContentRichlyEditable())
803 moveNodeOutOfAncestor(*node, *headerElement, insertedNodes);
804 else {
805 auto newSpanElement = makeRefPtr(replaceElementWithSpanPreservingChildrenAndAttributes(downcast<HTMLElement>(*node)));
806 insertedNodes.didReplaceNode(node.get(), newSpanElement.get());
807 }
808 }
809 }
810 }
811}

813static inline bool hasRenderedText(const Text& text)
814{
815 return text.renderer() && text.renderer()->hasRenderedText();
816}
817
818void ReplaceSelectionCommand::moveNodeOutOfAncestor(Node& node, Node& ancestor, InsertedNodes& insertedNodes)
819{
820 Ref<Node> protectedNode = node;
821 Ref<Node> protectedAncestor = ancestor;
822
823 VisiblePosition positionAtEndOfNode = lastPositionInOrAfterNode(&node);
824 VisiblePosition lastPositionInParagraph = lastPositionInNode(&ancestor);
825 if (positionAtEndOfNode == lastPositionInParagraph) {
826 removeNode(node);
827 if (ancestor.nextSibling())
828 insertNodeBefore(WTFMove(protectedNode), *ancestor.nextSibling());
829 else
830 appendNode(WTFMove(protectedNode), *ancestor.parentNode());
831 } else {
832 RefPtr<Node> nodeToSplitTo = splitTreeToNode(node, ancestor, true);
833 removeNode(node);
834 if (nodeToSplitTo)
835 insertNodeBefore(WTFMove(protectedNode), *nodeToSplitTo);
836 }
837
838 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
839
840 bool safeToRemoveAncestor = true;
841 for (auto child = makeRefPtr(ancestor.firstChild()); child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
842 if (is<Text>(child) && hasRenderedText(downcast<Text>(*child))) {
843 safeToRemoveAncestor = false;
844 break;
845 }
846
847 if (is<Element>(child)) {
848 safeToRemoveAncestor = false;
849 break;
850 }
851 }
852
853 if (safeToRemoveAncestor) {
854 insertedNodes.willRemoveNode(&ancestor);
855 removeNode(ancestor);
856 }
857}
858
859void ReplaceSelectionCommand::removeUnrenderedTextNodesAtEnds(InsertedNodes& insertedNodes)
860{
861 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
862
863 auto lastLeafInserted = makeRefPtr(insertedNodes.lastLeafInserted());
864 if (is<Text>(lastLeafInserted) && !hasRenderedText(downcast<Text>(*lastLeafInserted))
865 && !enclosingElementWithTag(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(lastLeafInserted.get()), selectTag)
866 && !enclosingElementWithTag(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(lastLeafInserted.get()), scriptTag)) {
867 insertedNodes.willRemoveNode(lastLeafInserted.get());
868 removeNode(*lastLeafInserted);
869 }
870
871 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
872
873 // We don't have to make sure that firstNodeInserted isn't inside a select or script element
874 // because it is a top level node in the fragment and the user can't insert into those elements.
875 auto firstNodeInserted = makeRefPtr(insertedNodes.firstNodeInserted());
876 if (is<Text>(firstNodeInserted) && !hasRenderedText(downcast<Text>(*firstNodeInserted))) {
877 insertedNodes.willRemoveNode(firstNodeInserted.get());
878 removeNode(*firstNodeInserted);
879 }
880}

886 return enclosingSelect ? lastPositionInOrAfterNode(enclosingSelect.get()) : m_endOfInsertedContent;

893
894// Remove style spans before insertion if they are unnecessary. It's faster because we'll
895// avoid doing a layout.
896static bool handleStyleSpansBeforeInsertion(ReplacementFragment& fragment, const Position& insertionPos)
897{
898 auto topNode = makeRefPtr(fragment.firstChild());
899
900 // Handling the case where we are doing Paste as Quotation or pasting into quoted content is more complicated (see handleStyleSpans)
901 // and doesn't receive the optimization.
902 if (isMailPasteAsQuotationNode(topNode.get()) || enclosingNodeOfType(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(topNode.get()), isMailBlockquote, CanCrossEditingBoundary))
903 return false;
904
905 // Either there are no style spans in the fragment or a WebKit client has added content to the fragment
906 // before inserting it. Look for and handle style spans after insertion.
907 if (!isLegacyAppleStyleSpan(topNode.get()))
908 return false;
909
910 auto& wrappingStyleSpan = downcast<HTMLElement>(*topNode);
911 auto styleAtInsertionPos = EditingStyle::create(insertionPos.parentAnchoredEquivalent());
912 String styleText = styleAtInsertionPos->style()->asText();
913
914 // FIXME: This string comparison is a naive way of comparing two styles.
915 // We should be taking the diff and check that the diff is empty.
916 if (styleText != wrappingStyleSpan.getAttribute(styleAttr))
917 return false;
918
919 fragment.removeNodePreservingChildren(wrappingStyleSpan);
920 return true;
921}
922
923// At copy time, WebKit wraps copied content in a span that contains the source document's
924// default styles. If the copied Range inherits any other styles from its ancestors, we put
925// those styles on a second span.
926// This function removes redundant styles from those spans, and removes the spans if all their
927// styles are redundant.
928// We should remove the Apple-style-span class when we're done, see <rdar://problem/5685600>.
929// We should remove styles from spans that are overridden by all of their children, either here
930// or at copy time.
931void ReplaceSelectionCommand::handleStyleSpans(InsertedNodes& insertedNodes)
932{
933 RefPtr<HTMLElement> wrappingStyleSpan;
934 // The style span that contains the source document's default style should be at
935 // the top of the fragment, but Mail sometimes adds a wrapper (for Paste As Quotation),
936 // so search for the top level style span instead of assuming it's at the top.
937 for (auto node = makeRefPtr(insertedNodes.firstNodeInserted()); node; node = NodeTraversal::next(*node)) {
938 if (isLegacyAppleStyleSpan(node.get())) {
939 wrappingStyleSpan = static_pointer_cast<HTMLElement>(WTFMove(node));
940 break;
941 }
942 }
943
944 // There might not be any style spans if we're pasting from another application or if
945 // we are here because of a document.execCommand("InsertHTML", ...) call.
946 if (!wrappingStyleSpan)
947 return;
948
949 auto style = EditingStyle::create(wrappingStyleSpan->inlineStyle());
950 auto context = makeRefPtr(wrappingStyleSpan->parentNode());
951
952 // If Mail wraps the fragment with a Paste as Quotation blockquote, or if you're pasting into a quoted region,
953 // styles from blockquoteNode are allowed to override those from the source document, see <rdar://problem/4930986> and <rdar://problem/5089327>.
954 RefPtr<Node> blockquoteNode;
955 if (isMailPasteAsQuotationNode(context.get()))
956 blockquoteNode = context;
957 else
958 blockquoteNode = enclosingNodeOfType(firstPositionInNode(context.get()), isMailBlockquote, CanCrossEditingBoundary);
959
960 if (blockquoteNode)
961 context = document().documentElement();
962
963 // This operation requires that only editing styles to be removed from sourceDocumentStyle.
964 style->prepareToApplyAt(firstPositionInNode(context.get()));
965
966 // Remove block properties in the span's style. This prevents properties that probably have no effect
967 // currently from affecting blocks later if the style is cloned for a new block element during a future
968 // editing operation.
969 // FIXME: They *can* have an effect currently if blocks beneath the style span aren't individually marked
970 // with block styles by the editing engine used to style them. WebKit doesn't do this, but others might.
971 style->removeBlockProperties();
972
973 if (style->isEmpty() || !wrappingStyleSpan->firstChild()) {
974 insertedNodes.willRemoveNodePreservingChildren(wrappingStyleSpan.get());
975 removeNodePreservingChildren(*wrappingStyleSpan);
976 } else
977 setNodeAttribute(*wrappingStyleSpan, styleAttr, style->style()->asText());
978}
979
980void ReplaceSelectionCommand::mergeEndIfNeeded()
981{
982 if (!m_shouldMergeEnd)
983 return;
984
985 VisiblePosition startOfInsertedContent(positionAtStartOfInsertedContent());
986 VisiblePosition endOfInsertedContent(positionAtEndOfInsertedContent());
987
988 // Bail to avoid infinite recursion.
989 if (m_movingParagraph) {
990 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
991 return;
992 }
993
994 ASSERT(startOfInsertedContent.isNull() == endOfInsertedContent.isNull());
995 if (startOfInsertedContent.isNull() || endOfInsertedContent.isNull())
996 return;
997
998 // Merging two paragraphs will destroy the moved one's block styles. Always move the end of inserted forward
999 // to preserve the block style of the paragraph already in the document, unless the paragraph to move would
1000 // include the what was the start of the selection that was pasted into, so that we preserve that paragraph's
1001 // block styles.
1002 bool mergeForward = !(inSameParagraph(startOfInsertedContent, endOfInsertedContent) && !isStartOfParagraph(startOfInsertedContent));
1003
1004 VisiblePosition destination = mergeForward ? endOfInsertedContent.next() : endOfInsertedContent;
1005 VisiblePosition startOfParagraphToMove = mergeForward ? startOfParagraph(endOfInsertedContent) : endOfInsertedContent.next();
1006
1007 // Merging forward could result in deleting the destination anchor node.
1008 // To avoid this, we add a placeholder node before the start of the paragraph.
1009 if (endOfParagraph(startOfParagraphToMove) == destination) {
1010 auto placeholder = HTMLBRElement::create(document());
1011 insertNodeBefore(placeholder, *startOfParagraphToMove.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode());
1012 destination = VisiblePosition(positionBeforeNode(placeholder.ptr()));
1013 }
1014
1015 moveParagraph(startOfParagraphToMove, endOfParagraph(startOfParagraphToMove), destination);
1016
1017 // Merging forward will remove m_endOfInsertedContent from the document.
1018 if (mergeForward) {
1019 if (m_startOfInsertedContent.isOrphan())
1020 m_startOfInsertedContent = endingSelection().visibleStart().deepEquivalent();
1021 m_endOfInsertedContent = endingSelection().visibleEnd().deepEquivalent();
1022 // If we merged text nodes, m_endOfInsertedContent could be null. If this is the case, we use m_startOfInsertedContent.
1023 if (m_endOfInsertedContent.isNull())
1024 m_endOfInsertedContent = m_startOfInsertedContent;
1025 }
1026}
1027
1028static RefPtr<Node> enclosingInline(Node* node)
1029{
1030 auto currentNode = makeRefPtr(node);
1031 while (auto parent = makeRefPtr(currentNode->parentNode())) {
1032 if (isBlockFlowElement(*parent) || parent->hasTagName(bodyTag))
1033 return currentNode;
1034 // Stop if any previous sibling is a block.
1035 for (auto sibling = makeRefPtr(currentNode->previousSibling()); sibling; sibling = sibling->previousSibling()) {
1036 if (isBlockFlowElement(*sibling))
1037 return currentNode;
1038 }
1039 currentNode = parent;
1040 }
1041 return currentNode;
1042}
1043
1044static bool isInlineNodeWithStyle(const Node* node)
1045{
1046 // We don't want to skip over any block elements.
1047 if (isBlock(node))
1048 return false;
1049
1050 if (!node->isHTMLElement())
1051 return false;
1052
1053 // We can skip over elements whose class attribute is
1054 // one of our internal classes.
1055 const HTMLElement* element = static_cast<const HTMLElement*>(node);
1056 const AtomString& classAttributeValue = element->attributeWithoutSynchronization(classAttr);
1057 if (classAttributeValue == AppleTabSpanClass
1058 || classAttributeValue == AppleConvertedSpace
1059 || classAttributeValue == ApplePasteAsQuotation)
1060 return true;
1061
1062 return EditingStyle::elementIsStyledSpanOrHTMLEquivalent(*element);
1063}

1065inline Node* nodeToSplitToAvoidPastingIntoInlineNodesWithStyle(const Position& insertionPos)
1066{
1067 Node* containgBlock = enclosingBlock(insertionPos.containerNode());
1068 return highestEnclosingNodeOfType(insertionPos, isInlineNodeWithStyle, CannotCrossEditingBoundary, containgBlock);
1069}

1074 m_documentFragmentHTMLMarkup = serializeFragment(*m_documentFragment, SerializedNodes::SubtreeIncludingNode);
1075 ensureReplacementFragment();

1079static bool hasBlankLineBetweenParagraphs(Position& position)
1080{
1081 bool reachedBoundaryStart = false;
1082 bool reachedBoundaryEnd = false;
1083 VisiblePosition visiblePosition(position);
1084 VisiblePosition previousPosition = visiblePosition.previous(CannotCrossEditingBoundary, &reachedBoundaryStart);
1085 VisiblePosition nextPosition = visiblePosition.next(CannotCrossEditingBoundary, &reachedBoundaryStart);
1086 bool hasLineBeforePosition = isEndOfLine(previousPosition);
1087
1088 return !reachedBoundaryStart && !reachedBoundaryEnd && isBlankParagraph(visiblePosition) && hasLineBeforePosition && isStartOfLine(nextPosition);
1089}
1090
1091void ReplaceSelectionCommand::doApply()
1092{
1093 VisibleSelection selection = endingSelection();
1094 ASSERT(selection.isCaretOrRange());
1095 ASSERT(selection.start().deprecatedNode());
1096 if (selection.isNoneOrOrphaned() || !selection.start().deprecatedNode() || !selection.isContentEditable())
1097 return;
1098
1099 // In plain text only regions, we create style-less fragments, so the inserted content will automatically
1100 // match the style of the surrounding area and so we can avoid unnecessary work below for m_matchStyle.
1101 if (!selection.isContentRichlyEditable())
1102 m_matchStyle = false;
1103
1104 ReplacementFragment& fragment = *ensureReplacementFragment();
1105 if (performTrivialReplace(fragment))
1106 return;
1107
1108 // We can skip matching the style if the selection is plain text.
1109 if ((selection.start().deprecatedNode()->renderer() && selection.start().deprecatedNode()->renderer()->style().userModify() == UserModify::ReadWritePlaintextOnly)
1110 && (selection.end().deprecatedNode()->renderer() && selection.end().deprecatedNode()->renderer()->style().userModify() == UserModify::ReadWritePlaintextOnly))
1111 m_matchStyle = false;
1112
1113 if (m_matchStyle) {
1114 m_insertionStyle = EditingStyle::create(selection.start());
1115 m_insertionStyle->mergeTypingStyle(document());
1116 }
1117
1118 VisiblePosition visibleStart = selection.visibleStart();
1119 VisiblePosition visibleEnd = selection.visibleEnd();
1120
1121 bool selectionEndWasEndOfParagraph = isEndOfParagraph(visibleEnd);
1122 bool selectionStartWasStartOfParagraph = isStartOfParagraph(visibleStart);
1123
1124 auto startBlock = makeRefPtr(enclosingBlock(visibleStart.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode()));
1125
1126 Position insertionPos = selection.start();
1127 bool shouldHandleMailBlockquote = enclosingNodeOfType(insertionPos, isMailBlockquote, CanCrossEditingBoundary) && !m_ignoreMailBlockquote;
1128 bool selectionIsPlainText = !selection.isContentRichlyEditable();
1129 auto currentRoot = makeRefPtr(selection.rootEditableElement());
1130
1131 if ((selectionStartWasStartOfParagraph && selectionEndWasEndOfParagraph && !shouldHandleMailBlockquote)
1132 || startBlock == currentRoot || isListItem(startBlock.get()) || selectionIsPlainText)
1133 m_preventNesting = false;
1134
1135 if (selection.isRange()) {
1136 // When the end of the selection being pasted into is at the end of a paragraph, and that selection
1137 // spans multiple blocks, not merging may leave an empty line.
1138 // When the start of the selection being pasted into is at the start of a block, not merging
1139 // will leave hanging block(s).
1140 // Merge blocks if the start of the selection was in a Mail blockquote, since we handle
1141 // that case specially to prevent nesting.
1142 bool mergeBlocksAfterDelete = shouldHandleMailBlockquote || isEndOfParagraph(visibleEnd) || isStartOfBlock(visibleStart);
1143 // FIXME: We should only expand to include fully selected special elements if we are copying a
1144 // selection and pasting it on top of itself.
1145 // FIXME: capturing the content of this delete would allow a replace accessibility notification instead of a simple insert
1146 deleteSelection(false, mergeBlocksAfterDelete, true, false, true);
1147 visibleStart = endingSelection().visibleStart();
1148 if (fragment.hasInterchangeNewlineAtStart()) {
1149 if (isEndOfParagraph(visibleStart) && !isStartOfParagraph(visibleStart)) {
1150 if (!isEndOfEditableOrNonEditableContent(visibleStart))
1151 setEndingSelection(visibleStart.next());
1152 } else
1153 insertParagraphSeparator();
1154 }
1155 insertionPos = endingSelection().start();
1156 } else {
1157 ASSERT(selection.isCaret());
1158 if (fragment.hasInterchangeNewlineAtStart()) {
1159 VisiblePosition next = visibleStart.next(CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
1160 if (isEndOfParagraph(visibleStart) && !isStartOfParagraph(visibleStart) && next.isNotNull())
1161 setEndingSelection(next);
1162 else {
1163 insertParagraphSeparator();
1164 visibleStart = endingSelection().visibleStart();
1165 }
1166 }
1167 // We split the current paragraph in two to avoid nesting the blocks from the fragment inside the current block.
1168 // For example paste <div>foo</div><div>bar</div><div>baz</div> into <div>x^x</div>, where ^ is the caret.
1169 // As long as the div styles are the same, visually you'd expect: <div>xbar</div><div>bar</div><div>bazx</div>,
1170 // not <div>xbar<div>bar</div><div>bazx</div></div>.
1171 // Don't do this if the selection started in a Mail blockquote.
1172 if (m_preventNesting && !shouldHandleMailBlockquote && !isEndOfParagraph(visibleStart) && !isStartOfParagraph(visibleStart)) {
1173 insertParagraphSeparator();
1174 setEndingSelection(endingSelection().visibleStart().previous());
1175 }
1176 insertionPos = endingSelection().start();
1177 }
1178
1179 // We don't want any of the pasted content to end up nested in a Mail blockquote, so first break
1180 // out of any surrounding Mail blockquotes. Unless we're inserting in a table, in which case
1181 // breaking the blockquote will prevent the content from actually being inserted in the table.
1182 if (shouldHandleMailBlockquote && m_preventNesting && !(enclosingNodeOfType(insertionPos, &isTableStructureNode))) {
1183 applyCommandToComposite(BreakBlockquoteCommand::create(document()));
1184 // This will leave a br between the split.
1185 if (auto br = makeRefPtr(endingSelection().start().deprecatedNode())) {
1186 ASSERT(br->hasTagName(brTag));
1187 insertionPos = positionInParentBeforeNode(br.get());
1188 removeNode(*br);
1189 }
1190 }
1191
1192 // Inserting content could cause whitespace to collapse, e.g. inserting <div>foo</div> into hello^ world.
1193 prepareWhitespaceAtPositionForSplit(insertionPos);
1194
1195 // If the downstream node has been removed there's no point in continuing.
1196 if (!insertionPos.downstream().deprecatedNode())
1197 return;
1198
1199 // NOTE: This would be an incorrect usage of downstream() if downstream() were changed to mean the last position after
1200 // p that maps to the same visible position as p (since in the case where a br is at the end of a block and collapsed
1201 // away, there are positions after the br which map to the same visible position as [br, 0]).
1202 RefPtr<Node> endBR = insertionPos.downstream().deprecatedNode()->hasTagName(brTag) ? insertionPos.downstream().deprecatedNode() : nullptr;
1203 VisiblePosition originalVisPosBeforeEndBR;
1204 if (endBR)
1205 originalVisPosBeforeEndBR = VisiblePosition(positionBeforeNode(endBR.get())).previous();
1206
1207 RefPtr<Node> insertionBlock = enclosingBlock(insertionPos.deprecatedNode());
1208
1209 // Adjust insertionPos to prevent nesting.
1210 // If the start was in a Mail blockquote, we will have already handled adjusting insertionPos above.
1211 if (m_preventNesting && insertionBlock && !isTableCell(insertionBlock.get()) && !shouldHandleMailBlockquote) {
1212 ASSERT(insertionBlock != currentRoot);
1213 VisiblePosition visibleInsertionPos(insertionPos);
1214 if (isEndOfBlock(visibleInsertionPos) && !(isStartOfBlock(visibleInsertionPos) && fragment.hasInterchangeNewlineAtEnd()))
1215 insertionPos = positionInParentAfterNode(insertionBlock.get());
1216 else if (isStartOfBlock(visibleInsertionPos))
1217 insertionPos = positionInParentBeforeNode(insertionBlock.get());
1218 }
1219
1220 // Paste at start or end of link goes outside of link.
1221 insertionPos = positionAvoidingSpecialElementBoundary(insertionPos);
1222
1223 // FIXME: Can this wait until after the operation has been performed? There doesn't seem to be
1224 // any work performed after this that queries or uses the typing style.
1225 document().selection().clearTypingStyle();
1226
1227 // We don't want the destination to end up inside nodes that weren't selected. To avoid that, we move the
1228 // position forward without changing the visible position so we're still at the same visible location, but
1229 // outside of preceding tags.
1230 insertionPos = positionAvoidingPrecedingNodes(insertionPos);
1231
1232 // Paste into run of tabs splits the tab span.
1233 insertionPos = positionOutsideTabSpan(insertionPos);
1234
1235 bool hasBlankLinesBetweenParagraphs = hasBlankLineBetweenParagraphs(insertionPos);
1236 bool handledStyleSpans = handleStyleSpansBeforeInsertion(fragment, insertionPos);
1237 bool needsColorTransformed = fragmentNeedsColorTransformed(fragment, insertionPos);
1238
1239 // We're finished if there is nothing to add.
1240 if (fragment.isEmpty() || !fragment.firstChild())
1241 return;
1242
1243 // If we are not trying to match the destination style we prefer a position
1244 // that is outside inline elements that provide style.
1245 // This way we can produce a less verbose markup.
1246 // We can skip this optimization for fragments not wrapped in one of
1247 // our style spans and for positions inside list items
1248 // since insertAsListItems already does the right thing.
1249 if (!m_matchStyle && !enclosingList(insertionPos.containerNode())) {
1250 if (auto containerNode = makeRefPtr(insertionPos.containerNode())) {
1251 if (containerNode->isTextNode() && insertionPos.offsetInContainerNode() && !insertionPos.atLastEditingPositionForNode()) {
1252 splitTextNode(*insertionPos.containerText(), insertionPos.offsetInContainerNode());
1253 insertionPos = firstPositionInNode(insertionPos.containerNode());
1254 }
1255 }
1256
1257 if (RefPtr<Node> nodeToSplitTo = nodeToSplitToAvoidPastingIntoInlineNodesWithStyle(insertionPos)) {
1258 if (nodeToSplitTo->parentNode() && insertionPos.containerNode() != nodeToSplitTo->parentNode()) {
1259 auto splitStart = makeRefPtr(insertionPos.computeNodeAfterPosition());
1260 if (!splitStart)
1261 splitStart = insertionPos.containerNode();
1262 ASSERT(splitStart);
1263 nodeToSplitTo = splitTreeToNode(*splitStart, *nodeToSplitTo->parentNode()).get();
1264 insertionPos = positionInParentBeforeNode(nodeToSplitTo.get());
1265 }
1266 }
1267 }
1268
1269 // FIXME: When pasting rich content we're often prevented from heading down the fast path by style spans. Try
1270 // again here if they've been removed.
1271
1272 // 1) Insert the content.
1273 // 2) Remove redundant styles and style tags, this inner <b> for example: <b>foo <b>bar</b> baz</b>.
1274 // 3) Merge the start of the added content with the content before the position being pasted into.
1275 // 4) Do one of the following: a) expand the last br if the fragment ends with one and it collapsed,
1276 // b) merge the last paragraph of the incoming fragment with the paragraph that contained the
1277 // end of the selection that was pasted into, or c) handle an interchange newline at the end of the
1278 // incoming fragment.
1279 // 5) Add spaces for smart replace.
1280 // 6) Select the replacement if requested, and match style if requested.
1281
1282 InsertedNodes insertedNodes;
1283 RefPtr<Node> refNode = fragment.firstChild();
1284 RefPtr<Node> node = refNode->nextSibling();
1285
1286 if (refNode)
1287 fragment.removeNode(*refNode);
1288
1289 auto blockStart = makeRefPtr(enclosingBlock(insertionPos.deprecatedNode()));
1290 bool isInsertingIntoList = (isListHTMLElement(refNode.get()) || (isLegacyAppleStyleSpan(refNode.get()) && isListHTMLElement(refNode->firstChild())))
1291 && blockStart && blockStart->renderer()->isListItem();
1292 if (isInsertingIntoList)
1293 refNode = insertAsListItems(downcast<HTMLElement>(*refNode), blockStart.get(), insertionPos, insertedNodes);
1294 else if (isEditablePosition(insertionPos)) {
1295 insertNodeAt(*refNode, insertionPos);
1296 insertedNodes.respondToNodeInsertion(refNode.get());
1297 }
1298
1299 // Mutation events (bug 22634) may have already removed the inserted content
1300 if (!refNode->isConnected())
1301 return;
1302
1303 bool plainTextFragment = isPlainTextMarkup(refNode.get());
1304
1305 while (node) {
1306 RefPtr<Node> next = node->nextSibling();
1307 fragment.removeNode(*node);
1308 insertNodeAfter(*node, *refNode);
1309 insertedNodes.respondToNodeInsertion(node.get());
1310
1311 // Mutation events (bug 22634) may have already removed the inserted content
1312 if (!node->isConnected())
1313 return;
1314
1315 refNode = node;
1316 if (node && plainTextFragment)
1317 plainTextFragment = isPlainTextMarkup(node.get());
1318 node = next;
1319 }
1320
1321 if (insertedNodes.isEmpty())
1322 return;
1323 removeUnrenderedTextNodesAtEnds(insertedNodes);
1324
1325 if (!handledStyleSpans)
1326 handleStyleSpans(insertedNodes);
1327
1328 // Mutation events (bug 20161) may have already removed the inserted content
1329 if (insertedNodes.isEmpty())
1330 return;
1331 if (!insertedNodes.firstNodeInserted()->isConnected())
1332 return;
1333
1334 VisiblePosition startOfInsertedContent = firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(insertedNodes.firstNodeInserted());
1335
1336 // We inserted before the insertionBlock to prevent nesting, and the content before the insertionBlock wasn't in its own block and
1337 // didn't have a br after it, so the inserted content ended up in the same paragraph.
1338 if (!startOfInsertedContent.isNull() && insertionBlock && insertionPos.deprecatedNode() == insertionBlock->parentNode() && (unsigned)insertionPos.deprecatedEditingOffset() < insertionBlock->computeNodeIndex() && !isStartOfParagraph(startOfInsertedContent))
1339 insertNodeAt(HTMLBRElement::create(document()), startOfInsertedContent.deepEquivalent());
1340
1341 if (endBR && (plainTextFragment || shouldRemoveEndBR(endBR.get(), originalVisPosBeforeEndBR))) {
1342 auto parent = makeRefPtr(endBR->parentNode());
1343 insertedNodes.willRemoveNode(endBR.get());
1344 removeNode(*endBR);
1345 document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1346 if (auto nodeToRemove = makeRefPtr(highestNodeToRemoveInPruning(parent.get()))) {
1347 insertedNodes.willRemovePossibleAncestorNode(nodeToRemove.get());
1348 removeNode(*nodeToRemove);
1349 }
1350 }
1351
1352 if (insertedNodes.isEmpty())
1353 return;
1354
1355 makeInsertedContentRoundTrippableWithHTMLTreeBuilder(insertedNodes);
1356 if (insertedNodes.isEmpty())
1357 return;
1358 if (!insertedNodes.firstNodeInserted()->isConnected())
1359 return;
1360
1361 if (needsColorTransformed)
1362 inverseTransformColor(insertedNodes);
1363
1364 removeRedundantStylesAndKeepStyleSpanInline(insertedNodes);
1365 if (insertedNodes.isEmpty())
1366 return;
1367
1368 if (m_sanitizeFragment)
1369 applyCommandToComposite(SimplifyMarkupCommand::create(document(), insertedNodes.firstNodeInserted(), insertedNodes.pastLastLeaf()));
1370
1371 // Setup m_startOfInsertedContent and m_endOfInsertedContent. This should be the last two lines of code that access insertedNodes.
1372 m_startOfInsertedContent = firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(insertedNodes.firstNodeInserted());
1373 m_endOfInsertedContent = lastPositionInOrAfterNode(insertedNodes.lastLeafInserted());
1374
1375 // Determine whether or not we should merge the end of inserted content with what's after it before we do
1376 // the start merge so that the start merge doesn't effect our decision.
1377 m_shouldMergeEnd = shouldMergeEnd(selectionEndWasEndOfParagraph);
1378
1379 if (shouldMergeStart(selectionStartWasStartOfParagraph, fragment.hasInterchangeNewlineAtStart(), shouldHandleMailBlockquote)) {
1380 VisiblePosition startOfParagraphToMove = positionAtStartOfInsertedContent();
1381 VisiblePosition destination = startOfParagraphToMove.previous();
1382 // We need to handle the case where we need to merge the end
1383 // but our destination node is inside an inline that is the last in the block.
1384 // We insert a placeholder before the newly inserted content to avoid being merged into the inline.
1385 Node* destinationNode = destination.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode();
1386 if (m_shouldMergeEnd && destinationNode != enclosingInline(destinationNode) && enclosingInline(destinationNode)->nextSibling())
1387 insertNodeBefore(HTMLBRElement::create(document()), *refNode);
1388
1389 // Merging the first paragraph of inserted content with the content that came
1390 // before the selection that was pasted into would also move content after
1391 // the selection that was pasted into if: only one paragraph was being pasted,
1392 // and it was not wrapped in a block, the selection that was pasted into ended
1393 // at the end of a block and the next paragraph didn't start at the start of a block.
1394 // Insert a line break just after the inserted content to separate it from what
1395 // comes after and prevent that from happening.
1396 VisiblePosition endOfInsertedContent = positionAtEndOfInsertedContent();
1397 if (startOfParagraph(endOfInsertedContent) == startOfParagraphToMove) {
1398 insertNodeAt(HTMLBRElement::create(document()), endOfInsertedContent.deepEquivalent());
1399 // Mutation events (bug 22634) triggered by inserting the <br> might have removed the content we're about to move
1400 if (!startOfParagraphToMove.deepEquivalent().anchorNode()->isConnected())
1401 return;
1402 }
1403
1404 // FIXME: Maintain positions for the start and end of inserted content instead of keeping nodes. The nodes are
1405 // only ever used to create positions where inserted content starts/ends.
1406 moveParagraph(startOfParagraphToMove, endOfParagraph(startOfParagraphToMove), destination);
1407 m_startOfInsertedContent = endingSelection().visibleStart().deepEquivalent().downstream();
1408 if (m_endOfInsertedContent.isOrphan())
1409 m_endOfInsertedContent = endingSelection().visibleEnd().deepEquivalent().upstream();
1410 }
1411
1412 Position lastPositionToSelect;
1413 if (fragment.hasInterchangeNewlineAtEnd()) {
1414 VisiblePosition endOfInsertedContent = positionAtEndOfInsertedContent();
1415 VisiblePosition next = endOfInsertedContent.next(CannotCrossEditingBoundary);
1416
1417 if (selectionEndWasEndOfParagraph || !isEndOfParagraph(endOfInsertedContent) || next.isNull()) {
1418 if (!isStartOfParagraph(endOfInsertedContent)) {
1419 setEndingSelection(endOfInsertedContent);
1420 auto enclosingNode = makeRefPtr(enclosingBlock(endOfInsertedContent.deepEquivalent().deprecatedNode()));
1421 if (isListItem(enclosingNode.get())) {
1422 auto newListItem = HTMLLIElement::create(document());
1423 insertNodeAfter(newListItem.copyRef(), *enclosingNode);
1424 setEndingSelection(VisiblePosition(firstPositionInNode(newListItem.ptr())));
1425 } else {
1426 // Use a default paragraph element (a plain div) for the empty paragraph, using the last paragraph
1427 // block's style seems to annoy users.
1428 insertParagraphSeparator(true, !shouldHandleMailBlockquote && highestEnclosingNodeOfType(endOfInsertedContent.deepEquivalent(),
1429 isMailBlockquote, CannotCrossEditingBoundary, insertedNodes.firstNodeInserted()->parentNode()));
1430 }
1431
1432 // Select up to the paragraph separator that was added.
1433 lastPositionToSelect = endingSelection().visibleStart().deepEquivalent();
1434 updateNodesInserted(lastPositionToSelect.deprecatedNode());
1435 }
1436 } else {
1437 // Select up to the beginning of the next paragraph.
1438 lastPositionToSelect = next.deepEquivalent().downstream();
1439 }
1440
1441 } else
1442 mergeEndIfNeeded();
1443
1444 if (auto mailBlockquote = makeRefPtr(enclosingNodeOfType(positionAtStartOfInsertedContent().deepEquivalent(), isMailPasteAsQuotationNode)))
1445 removeNodeAttribute(downcast<Element>(*mailBlockquote), classAttr);
1446
1447 if (shouldPerformSmartReplace())
1448 addSpacesForSmartReplace();
1449
1450 if (!isInsertingIntoList && hasBlankLinesBetweenParagraphs && shouldPerformSmartParagraphReplace())
1451 addNewLinesForSmartReplace();
1452
1453 // If we are dealing with a fragment created from plain text
1454 // no style matching is necessary.
1455 if (plainTextFragment)
1456 m_matchStyle = false;
1457
1458 completeHTMLReplacement(lastPositionToSelect);
1459}

1463 if (isEditingTextAreaOrTextInput())
1464 return m_documentFragment->textContent();
1465
1466 return CompositeEditCommand::inputEventData();
1467}

1469RefPtr<DataTransfer> ReplaceSelectionCommand::inputEventDataTransfer() const
1470{
1471 if (isEditingTextAreaOrTextInput())
1472 return CompositeEditCommand::inputEventDataTransfer();
1473
1474 return DataTransfer::createForInputEvent(m_documentFragmentPlainText, m_documentFragmentHTMLMarkup);
1475}
1476
1477bool ReplaceSelectionCommand::shouldRemoveEndBR(Node* endBR, const VisiblePosition& originalVisPosBeforeEndBR)
1478{
1479 if (!endBR || !endBR->isConnected())
1480 return false;
1481
1482 VisiblePosition visiblePos(positionBeforeNode(endBR));
1483
1484 // Don't remove the br if nothing was inserted.
1485 if (visiblePos.previous() == originalVisPosBeforeEndBR)
1486 return false;
1487
1488 // Remove the br if it is collapsed away and so is unnecessary.
1489 if (!document().inNoQuirksMode() && isEndOfBlock(visiblePos) && !isStartOfParagraph(visiblePos))
1490 return true;
1491
1492 // A br that was originally holding a line open should be displaced by inserted content or turned into a line break.
1493 // A br that was originally acting as a line break should still be acting as a line break, not as a placeholder.
1494 return isStartOfParagraph(visiblePos) && isEndOfParagraph(visiblePos);
1495}

1497bool ReplaceSelectionCommand::shouldPerformSmartReplace() const
1498{
1499 if (!m_smartReplace)
1500 return false;
1501
1502 auto textControl = makeRefPtr(enclosingTextFormControl(positionAtStartOfInsertedContent().deepEquivalent()));
1503 if (is<HTMLInputElement>(textControl) && downcast<HTMLInputElement>(*textControl).isPasswordField())
1504 return false; // Disable smart replace for password fields.
1505
1506 return true;
1507}

1509bool ReplaceSelectionCommand::shouldPerformSmartParagraphReplace() const
1510{
1511 if (!m_smartReplace)
1512 return false;
1513
1514 if (!document().editingBehavior().shouldSmartInsertDeleteParagraphs())
1515 return false;
1516
1517 return true;
1518}

1520static bool isCharacterSmartReplaceExemptConsideringNonBreakingSpace(UChar32 character, bool previousCharacter)
1521{
1522 return isCharacterSmartReplaceExempt(character == noBreakSpace ? ' ' : character, previousCharacter);
1523}
1524
1525void ReplaceSelectionCommand::addNewLinesForSmartReplace()
1526{
1527 VisiblePosition startOfInsertedContent = positionAtStartOfInsertedContent();
1528 VisiblePosition endOfInsertedContent = positionAtEndOfInsertedContent();
1529
1530 bool isPastedContentEntireParagraphs = isStartOfParagraph(startOfInsertedContent) && isEndOfParagraph(endOfInsertedContent);
1531
1532 // If we aren't pasting a paragraph, no need to attempt to insert newlines.
1533 if (!isPastedContentEntireParagraphs)
1534 return;
1535
1536 bool reachedBoundaryStart = false;
1537 bool reachedBoundaryEnd = false;
1538 VisiblePosition positionBeforeStart = startOfInsertedContent.previous(CannotCrossEditingBoundary, &reachedBoundaryStart);
1539 VisiblePosition positionAfterEnd = endOfInsertedContent.next(CannotCrossEditingBoundary, &reachedBoundaryEnd);
1540
1541 if (!reachedBoundaryStart && !reachedBoundaryEnd) {
1542 if (!isBlankParagraph(positionBeforeStart) && !isBlankParagraph(startOfInsertedContent) && isEndOfLine(positionBeforeStart) && !isEndOfEditableOrNonEditableContent(positionAfterEnd) && !isEndOfEditableOrNonEditableContent(endOfInsertedContent)) {
1543 setEndingSelection(startOfInsertedContent);
1544 insertParagraphSeparator();
1545 auto newStart = endingSelection().visibleStart().previous(CannotCrossEditingBoundary, &reachedBoundaryStart);
1546 if (!reachedBoundaryStart)
1547 m_startOfInsertedContent = newStart.deepEquivalent();
1548 }
1549 }
1550
1551 reachedBoundaryStart = false;
1552 reachedBoundaryEnd = false;
1553 positionAfterEnd = endOfInsertedContent.next(CannotCrossEditingBoundary, &reachedBoundaryEnd);
1554 positionBeforeStart = startOfInsertedContent.previous(CannotCrossEditingBoundary, &reachedBoundaryStart);
1555
1556 if (!reachedBoundaryEnd && !reachedBoundaryStart) {
1557 if (!isBlankParagraph(positionAfterEnd) && !isBlankParagraph(endOfInsertedContent) && isStartOfLine(positionAfterEnd) && !isEndOfLine(positionAfterEnd) && !isEndOfEditableOrNonEditableContent(positionAfterEnd)) {
1558 setEndingSelection(endOfInsertedContent);
1559 insertParagraphSeparator();
1560 m_endOfInsertedContent = endingSelection().start();
1561 }
1562 }
1563}
1564
1565void ReplaceSelectionCommand::addSpacesForSmartReplace()
1566{
1567 VisiblePosition startOfInsertedContent = positionAtStartOfInsertedContent();
1568 VisiblePosition endOfInsertedContent = positionAtEndOfInsertedContent();
1569
1570 Position endUpstream = endOfInsertedContent.deepEquivalent().upstream();
1571 auto endNode = makeRefPtr(endUpstream.computeNodeBeforePosition());
1572 int endOffset = is<Text>(endNode) ? downcast<Text>(*endNode).length() : 0;
1573 if (endUpstream.anchorType() == Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor) {
1574 endNode = endUpstream.containerNode();
1575 endOffset = endUpstream.offsetInContainerNode();
1576 }
1577
1578 bool needsTrailingSpace = !isEndOfParagraph(endOfInsertedContent) && !isStartOfParagraph(endOfInsertedContent) && !isCharacterSmartReplaceExemptConsideringNonBreakingSpace(endOfInsertedContent.characterAfter(), false);
1579 if (needsTrailingSpace && endNode) {
1580 bool collapseWhiteSpace = !endNode->renderer() || endNode->renderer()->style().collapseWhiteSpace();
1581 if (is<Text>(*endNode)) {
1582 insertTextIntoNode(downcast<Text>(*endNode), endOffset, collapseWhiteSpace ? nonBreakingSpaceString() : " ");
1583 if (m_endOfInsertedContent.containerNode() == endNode)
1584 m_endOfInsertedContent.moveToOffset(m_endOfInsertedContent.offsetInContainerNode() + 1);
1585 } else {
1586 auto node = document().createEditingTextNode(collapseWhiteSpace ? nonBreakingSpaceString() : " ");
1587 insertNodeAfter(node.copyRef(), *endNode);
1588 updateNodesInserted(node.ptr());
1589 }
1590 }
1591
1592 document().updateLayout();
1593
1594 Position startDownstream = startOfInsertedContent.deepEquivalent().downstream();
1595 auto startNode = makeRefPtr(startDownstream.computeNodeAfterPosition());
1596 unsigned startOffset = 0;
1597 if (startDownstream.anchorType() == Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor) {
1598 startNode = startDownstream.containerNode();
1599 startOffset = startDownstream.offsetInContainerNode();
1600 }
1601
1602 bool needsLeadingSpace = !isStartOfParagraph(startOfInsertedContent) && !isEndOfParagraph(startOfInsertedContent) && !isCharacterSmartReplaceExemptConsideringNonBreakingSpace(startOfInsertedContent.previous().characterAfter(), true);
1603 if (needsLeadingSpace && startNode) {
1604 bool collapseWhiteSpace = !startNode->renderer() || startNode->renderer()->style().collapseWhiteSpace();
1605 if (is<Text>(*startNode)) {
1606 insertTextIntoNode(downcast<Text>(*startNode), startOffset, collapseWhiteSpace ? nonBreakingSpaceString() : " ");
1607 if (m_endOfInsertedContent.containerNode() == startNode && m_endOfInsertedContent.offsetInContainerNode())
1608 m_endOfInsertedContent.moveToOffset(m_endOfInsertedContent.offsetInContainerNode() + 1);
1609 } else {
1610 auto node = document().createEditingTextNode(collapseWhiteSpace ? nonBreakingSpaceString() : " ");
1611 // Don't updateNodesInserted. Doing so would set m_endOfInsertedContent to be the node containing the leading space,
1612 // but m_endOfInsertedContent is supposed to mark the end of pasted content.
1613 insertNodeBefore(node, *startNode);
1614 m_startOfInsertedContent = firstPositionInNode(node.ptr());
1615 }
1616 }
1617}
1618
1619void ReplaceSelectionCommand::completeHTMLReplacement(const Position &lastPositionToSelect)
1620{
1621 Position start = positionAtStartOfInsertedContent().deepEquivalent();
1622 Position end = positionAtEndOfInsertedContent().deepEquivalent();
1623
1624 // Mutation events may have deleted start or end
1625 if (start.isNotNull() && !start.isOrphan() && end.isNotNull() && !end.isOrphan()) {
1626 // FIXME (11475): Remove this and require that the creator of the fragment to use nbsps.
1627 rebalanceWhitespaceAt(start);
1628 rebalanceWhitespaceAt(end);
1629
1630 if (m_matchStyle) {
1631 ASSERT(m_insertionStyle);
1632 applyStyle(m_insertionStyle.get(), start, end);
1633 // applyStyle may clone content to new block wrappers and make anchor nodes orphan.
1634 if (start.isOrphan() || end.isOrphan()) {
1635 start = endingSelection().start();
1636 end = endingSelection().end();
1637 m_startOfInsertedContent = start;
1638 m_endOfInsertedContent = end;
1639 }
1640 }
1641
1642 if (lastPositionToSelect.isNotNull())
1643 end = lastPositionToSelect;
1644
1645 mergeTextNodesAroundPosition(start, end);
1646 mergeTextNodesAroundPosition(end, start);
1647 } else if (lastPositionToSelect.isNotNull())
1648 start = end = lastPositionToSelect;
1649 else
1650 return;
1651
1652 if (AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled() && editingAction() == EditAction::Paste)
1653 m_visibleSelectionForInsertedText = VisibleSelection(start, end);
1654
1655 if (m_selectReplacement)
1656 setEndingSelection(VisibleSelection(start, end, VisibleSelection::defaultAffinity, endingSelection().isDirectional()));
1657 else
1658 setEndingSelection(VisibleSelection(end, VisibleSelection::defaultAffinity, endingSelection().isDirectional()));
1659}
1660
1661void ReplaceSelectionCommand::mergeTextNodesAroundPosition(Position& position, Position& positionOnlyToBeUpdated)
1662{
1663 bool positionIsOffsetInAnchor = position.anchorType() == Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor;
1664 bool positionOnlyToBeUpdatedIsOffsetInAnchor = positionOnlyToBeUpdated.anchorType() == Position::PositionIsOffsetInAnchor;
1665 RefPtr<Text> text;
1666 if (positionIsOffsetInAnchor && is<Text>(position.containerNode()))
1667 text = downcast<Text>(position.containerNode());
1668 else {
1669 if (auto* before = position.computeNodeBeforePosition(); is<Text>(before))
1670 text = downcast<Text>(before);
1671 else if (auto* after = position.computeNodeAfterPosition(); is<Text>(after))
1672 text = downcast<Text>(after);
1673 }
1674 if (!text)
1675 return;
1676
1677 if (auto* previousSibling = text->previousSibling(); is<Text>(previousSibling)) {
1678 auto previous = makeRef(downcast<Text>(*previousSibling));
1679 insertTextIntoNode(*text, 0, previous->data());
1680
1681 if (positionIsOffsetInAnchor)
1682 position.moveToOffset(previous->length() + position.offsetInContainerNode());
1683 else
1684 updatePositionForNodeRemoval(position, previous.get());
1685
1686 if (positionOnlyToBeUpdatedIsOffsetInAnchor) {
1687 if (positionOnlyToBeUpdated.containerNode() == text)
1688 positionOnlyToBeUpdated.moveToOffset(previous->length() + positionOnlyToBeUpdated.offsetInContainerNode());
1689 else if (positionOnlyToBeUpdated.containerNode() == previous.ptr())
1690 positionOnlyToBeUpdated.moveToPosition(text.get(), positionOnlyToBeUpdated.offsetInContainerNode());
1691 } else
1692 updatePositionForNodeRemoval(positionOnlyToBeUpdated, previous.get());
1693
1694 removeNode(previous);
1695 }
1696 if (auto* nextSibling = text->nextSibling(); is<Text>(nextSibling)) {
1697 auto next = makeRef(downcast<Text>(*nextSibling));
1698 unsigned originalLength = text->length();
1699 insertTextIntoNode(*text, originalLength, next->data());
1700
1701 if (!positionIsOffsetInAnchor)
1702 updatePositionForNodeRemoval(position, next.get());
1703
1704 if (positionOnlyToBeUpdatedIsOffsetInAnchor && positionOnlyToBeUpdated.containerNode() == next.ptr())
1705 positionOnlyToBeUpdated.moveToPosition(text.get(), originalLength + positionOnlyToBeUpdated.offsetInContainerNode());
1706 else
1707 updatePositionForNodeRemoval(positionOnlyToBeUpdated, next.get());
1708
1709 removeNode(next);
1710 }
1711}
1712
1713static HTMLElement* singleChildList(HTMLElement& element)
1714{
1715 if (!element.hasOneChild())
1716 return nullptr;
1717
1718 auto child = makeRefPtr(element.firstChild());
1719 return isListHTMLElement(child.get()) ? &downcast<HTMLElement>(*child) : nullptr;
1720}
1721
1722static HTMLElement& deepestSingleChildList(HTMLElement& topLevelList)
1723{
1724 auto list = makeRefPtr(topLevelList);
1725 while (auto childList = singleChildList(*list))
1726 list = childList;
1727 return *list;
1728}
1729
1730// If the user is inserting a list into an existing list, instead of nesting the list,
1731// we put the list items into the existing list.
1732Node* ReplaceSelectionCommand::insertAsListItems(HTMLElement& passedListElement, Node* insertionBlock, const Position& insertPos, InsertedNodes& insertedNodes)
1733{
1734 Ref<HTMLElement> listElement = deepestSingleChildList(passedListElement);
1735
1736 bool isStart = isStartOfParagraph(insertPos);
1737 bool isEnd = isEndOfParagraph(insertPos);
1738 bool isMiddle = !isStart && !isEnd;
1739 auto lastNode = makeRefPtr(insertionBlock);
1740
1741 // If we're in the middle of a list item, we should split it into two separate
1742 // list items and insert these nodes between them.
1743 if (isMiddle) {
1744 int textNodeOffset = insertPos.offsetInContainerNode();
1745 if (is<Text>(*insertPos.deprecatedNode()) && textNodeOffset > 0)
1746 splitTextNode(downcast<Text>(*insertPos.deprecatedNode()), textNodeOffset);
1747 splitTreeToNode(*insertPos.deprecatedNode(), *lastNode, true);
1748 }
1749
1750 while (RefPtr<Node> listItem = listElement->firstChild()) {
1751 listElement->removeChild(*listItem);
1752 if (isStart || isMiddle) {
1753 insertNodeBefore(*listItem, *lastNode);
1754 insertedNodes.respondToNodeInsertion(listItem.get());
1755 } else if (isEnd) {
1756 insertNodeAfter(*listItem, *lastNode);
1757 insertedNodes.respondToNodeInsertion(listItem.get());
1758 lastNode = listItem.get();
1759 } else
1760 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1761 }
1762 if ((isStart || isMiddle) && lastNode->previousSibling())
1763 lastNode = lastNode->previousSibling();
1764 return lastNode.get();
1765}
1766
1767void ReplaceSelectionCommand::updateNodesInserted(Node *node)
1768{
1769 if (!node)
1770 return;
1771
1772 if (m_startOfInsertedContent.isNull())
1773 m_startOfInsertedContent = firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(node);
1774
1775 m_endOfInsertedContent = lastPositionInOrAfterNode(node->lastDescendant());
1776}
1777
1778ReplacementFragment* ReplaceSelectionCommand::ensureReplacementFragment()
1779{
1780 if (!m_replacementFragment)
1781 m_replacementFragment = makeUnique<ReplacementFragment>(m_documentFragment.get(), endingSelection());
1782 return m_replacementFragment.get();
1783}
1784
1785// During simple pastes, where we're just pasting a text node into a run of text, we insert the text node
1786// directly into the text node that holds the selection. This is much faster than the generalized code in
1787// ReplaceSelectionCommand, and works around <https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=6148> since we don't
1788// split text nodes.
1789bool ReplaceSelectionCommand::performTrivialReplace(const ReplacementFragment& fragment)
1790{
1791 if (!is<Text>(fragment.firstChild()) || fragment.firstChild() != fragment.lastChild())
1792 return false;
1793 auto textNode = makeRef(downcast<Text>(*fragment.firstChild()));
1794
1795 // FIXME: Would be nice to handle smart replace in the fast path.
1796 if (m_smartReplace || fragment.hasInterchangeNewlineAtStart() || fragment.hasInterchangeNewlineAtEnd())
1797 return false;
1798
1799 // e.g. when "bar" is inserted after "foo" in <div><u>foo</u></div>, "bar" should not be underlined.
1800 if (nodeToSplitToAvoidPastingIntoInlineNodesWithStyle(endingSelection().start()))
1801 return false;
1802
1803 RefPtr<Node> nodeAfterInsertionPos = endingSelection().end().downstream().anchorNode();
1804 // Our fragment creation code handles tabs, spaces, and newlines, so we don't have to worry about those here.
1805
1806 Position start = endingSelection().start();
1807 Position end = replaceSelectedTextInNode(textNode->data());
1808 if (end.isNull())
1809 return false;
1810
1811 if (nodeAfterInsertionPos && nodeAfterInsertionPos->parentNode() && nodeAfterInsertionPos->hasTagName(brTag)
1812 && shouldRemoveEndBR(nodeAfterInsertionPos.get(), positionBeforeNode(nodeAfterInsertionPos.get())))
1813 removeNodeAndPruneAncestors(*nodeAfterInsertionPos);
1814
1815 VisibleSelection selectionAfterReplace(m_selectReplacement ? start : end, end);
1816
1817 if (AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled() && editingAction() == EditAction::Paste)
1818 m_visibleSelectionForInsertedText = VisibleSelection(start, end);
1819
1820 setEndingSelection(selectionAfterReplace);
1821
1822 return true;
1823}
1824
1825std::optional<SimpleRange> ReplaceSelectionCommand::insertedContentRange() const
1826{
1827 return makeSimpleRange(m_startOfInsertedContent, m_endOfInsertedContent);
1828}
